Text:
Ramai juga yang cuba membandingkan dengan jenama atau model lain.

Dari segi teknikal, Apple Watch (AW) ni berbeza dari segmen jam tangan yang fokus pada kecerdasan seperti Garmin, Amazfit, Suunto dan sebagainya.

Sifat AW lebih kepada all-in-one.
Translated Text:
Many also try to compare with other brands or models.

From a technical point of view, this Apple Watch (AW) is different from the watch segment that focuses on intelligence such as Garmin, Amazfit, Suunto and so on.

The nature of AW is more of an all-in-one.

Text:
Tidak fokus pada sesuatu fungsi sahaja. Seperti jenama Garmin yang memang memfokuskan pada fungsi sukan.

Banyak kelebihan & fungsi yang lebih terperinci tentang sukan kalau guna Garmin.

Lebih tahan lasak dan rekaan yang berasaskan outdoor.
Translated Text:
Do not focus on a single function. Like the Garmin brand that really focuses on sports functions.

Many advantages & more detailed functions about sports if you use Garmin.

More durable and outdoor-based design.

Text:
Bila all-in-one, tidak semua fungsi difokuskan secara terperinci. Tapi kebanyakannya ada.

Kalau nak cari jam tangan ala-ala AW tapi bateri lebih tahan lama dan tak kisah mengenai ekosistem Apple, boleh cuba jenama HUAWEI atau Samsung.
Translated Text:
When all-in-one, not all functions are focused in detail. But most of them are there.

If you want to find an AW-style watch but the battery lasts longer and you don't care about the Apple ecosystem, you can try HUAWEI or Samsung brands.

Text: Kalau cari jam ala-ala Garmin tapi lebih harga berpatutan, boleh cuba jenama Amazfit atau Coroz.
Translated Text: If you're looking for a Garmin-style watch but more affordable, you can try the Amazfit or Coroz brands.

Text:

Lama-lama ia menjadi fenomena & banyak pengeluar mengeluarkan gaming chair berasaskan bucket seat kereta.

Antara syarikat terawal yang buat adalah DXRacer. https://t.co/sDf1s7b8cs

Gaming chair was originally created to play car games while holding the steering wheel. That's why his posture is like a car bucket seat.

Over time it became a phenomenon & Many manufacturers produce gaming chairs based on car bucket seats.

One of the earliest companies to do so was DXRacer. https://t.co/sDf1s7b8cs

Text:
2. Memandu di bahagian kiri, gear knob di kanan, tapi kedudukan pedal sama macam di Malaysia.

Hari pertama memang sangat kekok, tapi masuk hari ke-2 dah faham. Tapi tangan masih asyik nak masuk gear belah kiri üòÇ
Translated Text:
2. Driving on the left, gear knob on the right, but the pedal position is the same as in Malaysia.

The first day was really awkward, but by the 2nd day I understood. But the hand is still busy trying to get into the left gear üòÇ

Text:
3. Ikut speed limit kalau taknak kena saman, sebab harga saman boleh cecah beribu.

Setiap jalan memang banyak reminder speed limit. Highway 100KM/h, jalan kecil 30 ~ 60KM/h.

Pandu di Swiss memang kena banyak bersabar dan fokus pada reminder speed limit.
Translated Text:
3. Follow the speed limit if you don't want to be sued, because the price of a suit can reach thousands.

Every road has many speed limit reminders. Highway 100KM/h, small roads 30 ~ 60KM/h.

Driving in Switzerland really has to be patient and focus on the speed limit reminder.

Text:
4. Kalau dah ikut peraturan pemanduan, memang akan ada pemandu lain yang nak laju.

Kena hon, jari tengah dan lampu tinggi tu biasa. Kalau nak laju boleh je, tapi bahaya dan bayar la saman dia.
Translated Text:
4. If you follow the driving rules, there will indeed be other drivers who want to speed.

Horn, middle finger and high beam are normal. If you want to go fast, you can, but it's dangerous and you have to pay him.

Text:
5. Tak boleh parkir RV sesuka hati kalau taknak kena saman. Survey dulu harga parkir dan boleh tak parkir RV situ.

Tiket parkir dia pun tak murah. Setakat ni harga parkir aku kena sekitar CHF6~10.
Translated Text:
5. Can't park the RV as you like if you don't want to get sued. First survey the price of parking and whether it is possible to park the RV there.

His parking ticket is not cheap. So far, the price of parking is around CHF6~10.

Text:
6. RV aku bawa tu takde reverse camera dan sensor. Jadi, memang kena ada kawan untuk monitor dari belakang.

Bukan takat tengok bawah je, atas pun sama untuk elakkan kena ranting pokok sebab RV tinggi.
Translated Text:
6. The RV I brought does not have a reverse camera or sensor. So, you have to have a friend to monitor from behind.

It's not just about looking down, the top is the same to avoid hitting tree branches because the RV is high.

Text:
7. Fahamkan setiap benda teknikal, error dan solusi. Benda paling penting adalah elektrik dan gas untuk cas, masak dan pemanas.

Takde pemanas masa tidur malam memang satu yang mengerikan dan tak boleh tidur. Suhu boleh cecah negatif.
Translated Text:
7. Understand every technical thing, error and solution. The most important things are electricity and gas for charging, cooking and heating.

Not having a heater when going to bed at night is a terrible thing and you can't sleep. The temperature can reach negative.

Text:
Apa kelebihan 5G selain dari laju?

1. Latensi yang sangat rendah, 1ms saja

2. Menyokong lebih banyak peranti serentak & masih kekal laju

3. Sambungan dengan peranti, robotik, Ai dan IoT lebih lancar dan meluas

5G bukan hanya untuk layan video 1080p, tapi sampai 8K pun steady.
Translated Text:
What are the advantages of 5G apart from speed?

1. Very low latency, only 1ms

2. Support more simultaneous devices & still remain fast

3. Seamless and widespread connection with devices, robotics, Ai and IoT

5G is not only for serving 1080p video, but even up to 8K is steady.

Text:
Ada juga kekurangan dia...

1. Infra terhad, tak banyak kawasan yang sokong.

2. Risiko sekuriti dan kawalan data yang masih belum terjamin sepenuhnya.

3. Awalnya, langganan 5G mungkin berganda mahal berbanding 4G.

4. 5G akan kawal otak kita dan jadi zombie ü§£ü§£ü§£
Translated Text:
There are also his shortcomings...

1. Limited infrastructure, not many areas support it.

2. Risk of security and data control that has not yet been fully secured.

3. Initially, 5G subscriptions may be twice as expensive as 4G.

4. 5G will control our brains and become zombies ü§£ü§£ü§£

Text:
Rasanya masalah utama berbasikal di Malaysia bukan cuaca, tapi kemudahan seperti parkir, jalan yang baik dan mentaliti.

Sebab ramai je yang suka kayuh dan daj jadi trend sekarang.

Berbasikal adalah solusi terbaik untuk mengelak kesesakan dan parkir. https://t.co/i2gKAMrvd8
Translated Text:
It seems that the main problem with cycling in Malaysia is not the weather, but facilities such as parking, good roads and mentality.

Because there are many people who like paddling and it has become a trend now.

Cycling is the best solution to avoid congestion and parking. https://t.co/i2gKAMrvd8

Text:
Aku dah kayuh sekitar KL, tiada masalah dari segi cuaca. Lebih-lebih lagi kalau kayuh e-bike. Tak penat sangat dan kurang peluh.

Cuma masalah utama dia kemudahan dan jalan. Kadang kereta pun park dekat laluan basikal, susah untuk pengayuh nak keep dalam lane khas basikal.
Translated Text:
I have paddled around KL, no problem in terms of weather. Especially if riding an e-bike. Not very tired and less sweaty.

Only the main problem is the facilities and roads. Sometimes the car is parked near the bicycle path, it is difficult for the pedaler to keep in the dedicated bicycle lane.

Text:
Secara positifnya, akan lebih banyak pengeluar EV dan pelabur yang akan melihat peluang pasaran di Malaysia.

Dulu mungkin ada yang persoalkan kenapa Malaysia lambat berbanding Singapura atau negara lain.

Tapi bila dah mula, ada juga yang masih persoalkan.
Translated Text:
On a positive note, there will be more EV manufacturers and investors who will see the market opportunity in Malaysia.

In the past, some may have questioned why Malaysia is slow compared to Singapore or other countries.

But when it started, some still questioned it.

Text:
Untuk itu, ia kembali kepada paksi asal kenapa mahu beli kereta elektrik disebalik enjin petrol.

Bila dah buka peluang ini, ia langkah kecil untuk peluang yang lebih besar dan pelaburan dari luar pada masa hadapan.

Sebagai contoh...
Translated Text:
For that, it goes back to the original axis of why you want to buy an electric car behind a petrol engine.

Once this opportunity is opened, it is a small step for greater opportunities and investment from outside in the future.

For example...

Text:
Dulu kereta hybrid mahal, sekarang dah boleh dapat dengan harga yang berpatutan untuk teknologi ditawarkan.

Awal-awal EV mungkin mahal, lama-lama mungkin akan ada pengeluar yang akan memberi pilihan segmen lebih berpatutan.
Translated Text:
Hybrid cars used to be expensive, now you can get them at a reasonable price for the technology offered.

Early on EVs may be expensive, eventually there will be manufacturers that will provide more affordable segment options.

Text:
Dalam pembentangan bajet 2022 yang positif untuk kereta elektrik (EV), harap kerajaan dapat push EV di Malaysia.

Harap juga dapat perbanyakkan tempat khas untuk mengecas yang lebih mudah dan selesa.
Translated Text:
In the presentation of the 2022 budget that is positive for electric cars (EVs), I hope the government can push EVs in Malaysia.

Please also be able to increase the number of special places to charge that are easier and more comfortable.

Text:

Dah lebih 20 tahun, pertama kali monyet ni semua datang kawasan perumahan.
Translated Text:
The area behind my family's house used to be a forest and a place for monkeys.

But after the forest was cleared and a new residential area was created, the monkeys all came out to find food and shelter.

It's been more than 20 years, the first time all these monkeys came to the residential area.

Text:
Nampaknya masih ramai yang tak faham konsep IoT

Fungsi pintar sebenarnya adalah alternatif tambahan sahaja. Masih ada manual seperti kunci dan alat kawalan.

Kelebihan Smart Autogate ni misalnya lupa bawa kunci, nak buka dari jauh atau sebagai alternatif AIoT.
Translated Text:
It seems that there are still many who do not understand the concept of IoT

The smart function is actually just an additional alternative. There are still manuals such as keys and controls.

The advantage of this Smart Autogate is for example forgetting to bring the key, wanting to open it remotely or as an AIoT alternative.

Text:
IoT = Internet of Things.

Ia bukan sahaja pada barangan elektronik pintar, tapi merangkumi pelbagai perkara seperti kereta, mesin, robotik dan banyak lagi.

Makin hari sebenarnya banyak barang yang kita guna hari-hari jadi semakin pintar. Contoh paling mudah, berus gigi pintar.
Translated Text:
IoT = Internet of Things.

It is not only on smart electronic items, but includes various things such as cars, machines, robotics and many more.

More and more things that we use every day are getting smarter. The simplest example, a smart toothbrush.

Text:
Nampak riak wajah dari sedih & bertukar lega sebab penat mencari atas jalan naik motor.

Kat sini aku belajar tentang rezeki.

Jika hilang sesuatu milik kita atau hadapi kegagalan, kalau dah tertulis ada rezeki yang lebih baik, tetap akan dapat. Lambat atau cepat saja.

2/3
Translated Text:
See facial expressions from sad & changed relieved because tired of searching on the road riding a motorbike.

Here I learned about sustenance.

If we lose something that belongs to us or face failure, if it is written that there is a better sustenance, we will still get it. Slow or fast.

2/3

Text:
Kalau ada antara kita yang rasa hari ini adalah hari yang paling buruk dalam kehidupan, percayalah yang akan habuan terbaik suatu hari nanti.

Rezeki kita mungkin berbeza, tapi semuanya telah tertulis. Sabar dan teruskan usaha üòÑ

3/3
Translated Text:
If any of us feel that today is the worst day in life, believe that one day the best reward will come.

Our sustenance may be different, but everything is written. Be patient and keep trying üòÑ

3/3

Text:
Ikut pengalaman sendiri, masalah yang aku nampak :

1. Polisi baru di Shopee yang tidak boleh memilih kurier. Kuasa membeli di Shopee sekarang sangat kuat. Memang sedikit terkesan.

2. Penghantaran yang sedikit lambat berbanding kurier lain. Masalah ni dari dulu lagi.
Translated Text:
Follow my own experience, the problems I see:

1. The new policy at Shopee is that you cannot choose a courier. The power of buying on Shopee is now very strong. It is a little impressed.

2. Delivery is a little slow compared to other couriers. This is a problem from before.

Text:
3. Banyak pesaing baru yang menawarkan caj lebih murah dan penghantaran lebih laju.

4. Cawangan pesaing yang lebih banyak di sesuatu kawasan. Kurangnya kesesakan semasa penghantaran.

5. Penghantaran surat makin kurang disebabkan ramai beralih ke email, WhatsApp & lain-lain.
Translated Text:
3. Many new competitors who offer cheaper charges and faster delivery.

4. More competitor branches in an area. Less congestion during delivery.

5. Mail delivery is becoming less and less due to many switching to email, WhatsApp & others.

Text:
6. Kemudahan semasa penghantaran di kaunter agak leceh berbanding beberapa pesaing lain.

7. Ada juga cawangan yang banyak perkhidmatan lain yang merumitkan pelanggan untuk tujuan pengeposan saja. Sebab mereka mahu proses yang pantas.
Translated Text:
6. The convenience during delivery at the counter is a bit slow compared to some other competitors.

7. There are also branches that have many other services that complicate the customer for the purpose of posting only. Because they want a fast process.

Text:
8. Wujudnya penghantaran barang lebih pantas seperti Lalamove, Mrspeedy, Grab dan lain-lain yang lebih cepat.

Pos Laju kena ubah cara mereka beroperasi dan sesuaikan dengan keperluan masa kini.

Harga tinggi sikit pun, asalkan pantas dan memudahkan pelanggan tu penting.
Translated Text:
8. The existence of faster delivery of goods such as Lalamove, Mrspeedy, Grab and others that are faster.

Pos Laju has to change the way they operate and adapt to the needs of today.

Even if the price is a little high, as long as it's fast and makes it easy for the customer, that's important.

Text:
Maaf, silap pengiraan ni. Jumlah tontonan tidak menjamin pulangan yang tinggi, tapi masa tontonan & iklan yang dikira.

Ikut pengalaman YouTube sendiri, tak pernah lagi cecah jumlah tu walaupun views lebih 1M organik.

Estimate revenue tu mungkin keseluruhan video yg lain sekali.
Translated Text:
Sorry, the calculation is wrong. The number of views does not guarantee a high return, but the viewing time & calculated ads.

Follow YouTube's own experience, it has never reached that number even though it has more than 1M views organically.

The estimated revenue may be a whole other video.

Text:
Purata pendapatan juga bergantung pada betapa konsisten kita mencapai views & watch time yang tinggi tiap kali upload video baru.

Biasanya purata pendapatan :

100K views > RM900 ~ RM1,200
1M views > RM7K ~ RM9K

Purata ni bergantung pada channel, niche dan watch time.
Translated Text:
The average income also depends on how consistently we achieve views & high watch time every time a new video is uploaded.

Usually average income:

100K views > RM900 ~ RM1,200
1M views > RM7K ~ RM9K

This average depends on the channel, niche and watch time.

Text:
Kitorang yang develop sistem online ni pun ada beberapa orang yang jadi mangsa banjir.

Buka laptop buat coding ketika rumah tengah tenggelam, kena berpindah, takde letrik, uruskan family, kena cari makanan dsb.

Maaf, kalau tak dapat jawab soalan lanjut tentang ni.
Translated Text:
Even the people who developed this online system had some people who were victims of the flood.

Open the laptop to do coding when the house is sinking, you have to move, there is no electricity, take care of your family, you have to find food, etc.

Sorry, if I can't answer further questions about this.

Kos nak ganti sangat tinggi.

Itu tak termasuk kos baiki kereta dan motorsikal yang tenggelam.

The cost to replace is very high.

That does not include the cost of repairing sunken cars and motorcycles.

That's it.

Kita semua sedang diuji. Jangan makin jauh dari rahmat Allah.

In this prayer jama we combine Zohor-Asr and Maghrib-Isha' prayers in 1 time.

We are all being tested. Don't get further away from God's grace.

Text:
‚Ä¢ Bila air banjir dah paras buku lali, balik rumah sekali lagi untuk full bersihkan lumpur+kotoran kalau ada. Tolak keluar.

‚Ä¢ Kalau balik ketika air banjir dah kering sepenuhnya, lumpur akan penuh di dinding dan lantai.

‚Ä¢ Korang perlukan air yang sgt banyak nak bersihkan.
Translated Text:
‚Ä¢ When the flood water is ankle level, return home again to fully clean the mud + dirt if there is any. Push out.

‚Ä¢ If you return when the flood water has completely dried up, mud will fill the walls and floor.

‚Ä¢ You need a lot of water to clean.

Text:
‚Ä¢ Nak bersihkan rumah yang berlumpur (kering) memang sangat memenatkan. Seminggu tak siap.

‚Ä¢ Sukarelawan paling banyak diperlukan untuk bersihkan rumah berbanding waktu ini.

Ini pengalaman aku yang dah kerap hadapi banjir sebelum ini.

Begitulah.
Translated Text:
‚Ä¢ Cleaning a muddy (dry) house is really tiring. Not ready for a week.

‚Ä¢ More volunteers are needed to clean the house than at this time.

This is my experience as I have often faced floods before.

That's it.

Text:
Sebab ini kali-5 kampung banjir besar sejak aku kecil, jadi orang kampung dah tenang.

‚Ä¢ Dokumen penting selamatkan dulu.
‚Ä¢ Bawa kucing, lepaskan ayam dll.
‚Ä¢ Selamatkan kereta/motor. Sebab confirm air naik laju.
‚Ä¢ Naikkan barang elektrik ke tempat tinggi.
‚Ä¢ Matikan elektrik.
Translated Text:
Because this is the 5th time the village has been flooded since I was a child, so the villagers have calmed down.

‚Ä¢ Save important documents first.
‚Ä¢ Bring the cat, release the chicken etc.
‚Ä¢ Secure the car/motorcycle. Because confirm the water is rising fast.
‚Ä¢ Raise electrical items to a high place.
‚Ä¢ Turn off the electricity.

Text:
‚Ä¢ Kena pergi kedai cepat beli barang keperluan. Roti, sardin, air mineral dsb. Sebab confirm akan habis cepat.

‚Ä¢ Cari tempat selamat. Pusat Pemindahan Banjir, rumah adik beradik dsb. Sebab tandas 100% tak berfungsi. Susah untuk semua kalau tinggal dalam banjir.

Itulah.
Translated Text:
‚Ä¢ Have to go to the store quickly to buy necessities. Bread, sardines, mineral water etc. Because confirmation will run out quickly.

‚Ä¢ Find a safe place. Flood Evacuation Center, sibling's house etc. Because the toilet is 100% not working. It's hard for everyone to live in a flood.

That's it.

Text:
Orang bisnes ni sibuk.

Mereka biasanya bukan jenis yang mampu bangun malam tahajjud selalu, kerap berpuasa sunat, solat 5 waktu berjemaah di masjid dsb.

Tapi mereka ada kelebihan harta.

Dengan bayar zakat dan banyak sedekah, ia mungkin jadi asbab mereka ni ke syurga.
Translated Text:
Business people are busy.

They are usually not the type who are able to wake up on the night of tahajjud regularly, fast circumcision, pray 5 times in congregation at the mosque etc.

But they have a wealth advantage.

By paying zakat and a lot of alms, it might be their cause to go to heaven.

Text:
Kekadang, seronok bila singgah kedai makan, tahu kedai tu bayar zakat banyak.

Bila isi minyak, aku cari stesen minyak yang ownernya bayar zakat.

Lalu depan kilang kerepek, teringat owner bayar zakat puluh ribu.

Mereka semua unsung hero yang membantu Asnaf.

Begitulah.
Translated Text:
Sometimes, it's fun when you stop by a restaurant, knowing that the restaurant pays a lot of zakat.

When I fill up, I look for a gas station whose owner pays zakat.

Then in front of the chip factory, I remembered the owner paying zakat ten thousand.

They are all unsung heroes who help Asnaf.

That's it.

Text:
2. Makin ramai perlukan sumber makanan, tapi makin sikit supply.

3. Kita semakin bergantung kepada makanan import. Jumlah % makanan yg kita kena IMPORT untuk cukupkan keperluan penduduk Malaysia (2021).

Padi : 30%
Sayur : 60%
Buah-buahan : 30%
Daging : 80%

Ia trend meningkat.
Translated Text:
2. More and more people need food sources, but less and less supply.

3. We are increasingly dependent on imported food. The total % of food we have to IMPORT to meet the needs of the Malaysian population (2021).

Rice : 30%
Vegetables: 60%
Fruits : 30%
Meat: 80%

It's an increasing trend.

Text:
4. Mungkin tak lama lagi, kita bakal jadi seperti Singapore yang mengimport 90% makanan penduduk mereka.

5. Bila import, harga kena mengikut pasaran dunia. Kita dah tak boleh kawal.

6. Lagi merisaukan, setiap tahun makin sedikit orang muda berminat menceburi bidang pertanian.
Translated Text:
4. Maybe soon, we will become like Singapore which imports 90% of their population's food.

5. When importing, the price must be according to the world market. We can't control it anymore.

6. Worryingly, every year fewer young people are interested in farming.

Text:
7. Harga makanan bakal terus meningkat setiap tahun kalau tiada tindakan drastik dari kerajaan untuk tingkatkan local food production.

8. Kita terlalu kejar teknologi/industri hingga keperluan asas seperti sumber makanan asas terabai.

Ini sikit perkongsian conference harini.
Translated Text:
7. Food prices will continue to increase every year if there is no drastic action from the government to increase local food production.

8. We chase technology/industry so much that basic needs such as basic food sources are neglected.

This is a bit of sharing from today's conference.

Text:
Contoh.

Modal berniaga : RM100,000
Rugi : RM30,000
Balance : RM70,000

RM70,000 ini lebih dari Nisab (RM19,610), maka zakat masih WAJIB dikeluarkan.

Jadi walau dia RUGI RM30,000 pada tahun ini, dia masih ada RM70,000.

Dia tetap kena bayar zakat 2.5% iaitu RM1,750.
Translated Text:
Example.

Business capital: RM100,000
Loss : RM30,000
Balance: RM70,000

This RM70,000 is more than Nisab (RM19,610), so zakat still MUST be paid.

So even if he LOSES RM30,000 this year, he still has RM70,000.

He still has to pay 2.5% zakat which is RM1,750.

Text:
Tapi lebih menarik, bukan setakat RFID je.

Tapi PLUS ada guna kamera ANCR (no plat recognition) + TVC (toll validation centre) nak sahkan kenderaan yang lalu tol match dengan RFID yang ditampal.

Maksudnya kita selangkah ke arah gateless toll-gate macam di Singapore. https://t.co/Y8bimz6Zko
Translated Text:
But more interesting, not only RFID.

But PLUS uses the ANCR (no plate recognition) camera + TVC (toll validation center) to verify that vehicles passing through the toll match match the affixed RFID.

It means we are one step towards a gateless toll-gate like in Singapore. https://t.co/Y8bimz6Zko

Text:
Antara penghalang kita nak guna gateless toll sebelum ni nombor plat kereta terlalu fancy.

Kalau nombor plat standard (saiz dan font) macam negara maju, mudah AI nak detect. Tak perlukan manual validation TVC tu.

Tapi itulah. Takkan kereta mewah/sport, nombor plat besar kan? üòé
Translated Text:
One of the barriers to using gateless toll before is that the car's license plate number is too fancy.

If the number plate is standard (size and font) like developed countries, it is easy for AI to detect. There is no need for manual validation of the TVC.

But that's it. Not luxury/sports cars, big license plates right? üòé

Text:
Kad Kredit diterima untuk bayaran zakat sejak sekian lama melalui kaunter.

Sebab pegawai boleh tapis manual kad kredit islamik vs konvensional.

Tapi bila online, sistem payment tak boleh bezakan nombor kad Islamik. Bila dah ada mekanisma tapisan, baru boleh guna bayar zakat.
Translated Text:
Credit cards have been accepted for zakat payments for a long time over the counter.

Because officials can manually filter Islamic vs conventional credit cards.

But when online, the payment system cannot distinguish Islamic card numbers. When there is a screening mechanism, it can be used to pay zakat.

Text:
Pernah duduk rumah ada swimming pool, kemudahan lain lengkap & density penduduk rendah.

Tapi suraunya kosong dan sunyi. Lepas awak azan, awak juga jadi imam. Kadangkala takde makmum hatta solat maghrib.

Muslim ada 40% kat situ.

Tak kena dengan jiwa. Ada rasa kekosongan.
Translated Text:
Ever lived in a house with a swimming pool, other complete facilities & low population density.

But the surau was empty and quiet. After you call to prayer, you also become an imam. Sometimes there is no makmum, not even Maghrib prayer.

There are 40% Muslims there.

It doesn't touch the soul. There is a sense of emptiness.

Text:
Bagi muslim, aku rasa kena pertimbangkan perumahan yang ada surau/masjid walaupun tak terlalu dekat.

Maksudnya masih boleh hadir solat berjemaah, solat Jumaat dan dengar pengajian agama.

Faktor ini bantu dekatkan kita dengan agama ketika usia dah semakin lanjut kelak.

Itulah.
Translated Text:
For Muslims, I think I have to consider housing that has a surau/mosque even if it's not too close.

This means that you can still attend congregational prayers, Friday prayers and listen to religious studies.

This factor helps bring us closer to religion when we get older.

That's it.

Semoga Allah pelihara iman kita sampailah kita mati kelak. Semoga pengakhiran yang baik-baik untuk kita dan keluarga kita.

Such is our faith. Sometimes it goes up and down.

When you feel that way, don't leave obligatory worship. It is our link with the creator.

May God protect our faith until we die. Hopefully a good ending for us and our family.

Text:
Kalau kita benar-benar mahu, 1-2 minggu boleh faham semuanya. Ia kekal sampai mati.

Ia sangat membantu kita kusyuk dalam solat.

Orang awam belajar Arabic bukan sampai nak bercakap/menulis bahasa arab.

Cukup faham serba sedikit bacaan solat dan apa yang kita doa kepada Allah.
Translated Text:
If we really want, 1-2 weeks can understand everything. It remains until death.

It helps us a lot in prayer.

Ordinary people learn Arabic not until they want to speak/write Arabic.

It is enough to understand a little bit of prayer readings and what we pray to God.

Text:
**Update**

Tadi jumpa makna bacaan dalam Solat dalam Bahasa Melayu.

‚Ä¢ Doa Iftitah.
‚Ä¢ Surah Al-Fatihah.

Mungkin boleh cuba hafal sikit-sikit. 1 hari satu pun sudah memadai. Sikit je tu. https://t.co/UvogdLbjWJ

‚Ä¢ Sujud

Text:
Kadangkala pelik juga sahabat Sekolah Pondok yang beriya-iya pertahankan ‚Äòguru‚Äô mereka yang memang terang-terang tersilap sebar benda salah.

Ketika Majlis Maulid bukan main mengaku CINTAKAN NABI.

Tapi semangat masa berqasidah je. Bila cuba tegakkan sunnah sebenar, dibantah.
Translated Text:
Sometimes it's also strange friends of Pondok School who defend their 'teacher' who is clearly wrong and spreading wrong things.

When the Mawlid ceremony is not a joke, confessing the love of the prophet.

But the spirit of the time is qasidah. When you try to uphold the true sunnah, you are opposed.

Text:
Ya, mereka mungkin ada sedikit ilmu dan ada sumbangan kepada masyarakat.

Tapi dalam agama ni, kita kena pertahankan Nabi melebihi guru kita.

Kalau tak, itulah satu tanda kita TAKSUB.

Bab agama ni jangan malu mengaku silap. Memang kita semua tidak maksum.
Translated Text:
Yes, they may have some knowledge and contribute to society.

But in this religion, we have to protect the Prophet more than our teachers.

If not, that's a sign that we are OBSESSED.

Don't be ashamed to admit that you are wrong about religion. We are all not infallible.

Text:
Berpihaklah kepada kebenaran.

Teliti dalil sahih yang ada. Semangat cinta nabi bukan hanya pada cara berpakaian.

Tapi.

Lebih penting bab ibadah kena usaha cari yang paling hampir dengan yang diajar Rasulullah.

Jangan dikaburi ketaksuban kepada guru. Teruskan tuntut ilmu.
Translated Text:
Stand up for the truth.

Examine the valid arguments that are available. The spirit of the prophet's love is not only in the way of dressing.

But.

It is more important to try to find the closest thing to what the Messenger of Allah taught about worship.

Don't be blinded by obsession with the teacher. Keep seeking knowledge.

Text:
Alangkah pelik kita.

Mereka yang cuba betulkan agama ini supaya ikut selari dengan ibadah Rasulullah dilabel Wahhabi.

Tapi.

Mereka yang bersungguh-sungguh pertahankan amalan tok guru yang Rasulullah langsung tidak buat, dilihat sebagai pencinta sunnah Nabi sebenar.

Terbalik.
Translated Text:
How strange we are.

Those who try to correct this religion so that it follows the worship of the Prophet are labeled Wahhabi.

But.

Those who earnestly defend the practices of teachers that the Messenger of Allah did not do, are seen as true lovers of the Prophet's Sunnah.

Inverted.

Text:
Ini sebab utama aku dah jarang tengok TikTok sekarang.

Attention span makin rendah.

Dah makin susah nak duduk 1-2 jam dengar ceramah, hatta ceramah di Youtube.

Makin sukar nak fokus baca buku 30-40 minit.

Scroll hampir sejam tapi tak ingat langsung apa benda yang dilihat.
Translated Text:
This is the main reason I rarely watch TikTok now.

Attention span is getting lower.

It's getting harder to sit for 1-2 hours listening to lectures, even lectures on YouTube.

It's getting harder to focus on reading a book for 30-40 minutes.

I scrolled for almost an hour but I can't remember exactly what I saw.

Text:
Dopamine tu memang real. Ramai susah nak berhenti scroll dan tak sedar habiskan masa terlalu lama.

Sebab alghorithm TikTok sangat powerful.

Sebelum jejaskan mental, baik limitkan dan belajar kawal.

Cuba tengok video 30 minit tanpa buat apa-apa.

Berapa lama korang mampu fokus?
Translated Text:
Dopamine is real. Many people find it hard to stop scrolling and don't realize they spend too much time.

Because the TikTok algorithm is very powerful.

Before it affects you mentally, limit it and learn to control it.

Try watching a 30-minute video without doing anything.

How long can you focus?

Text:
*Update.

Kenapa pelajar asnaf tak boleh mohon?

Bagi pelajar IPT di kalangan Asnaf Zakat di IPT awam atau pun swasta mereka dapat bantuan:

‚Ä¢ Yuran Pengajian
‚Ä¢ Belanja persediaan masuk IPT
‚Ä¢ Wang Saku setiap bulan
‚Ä¢ Bayaran Penginapan
‚Ä¢ Elaun Buku

Sebab tu tak layak. https://t.co/tLBCNxr47P

*Update.

Why can't asnaf students apply?

For IPT students among Asnaf Zakat in public or private IPT they can get help:

‚Ä¢ Tuition fees
‚Ä¢ IPT entrance preparation expenses
‚Ä¢ Pocket Money every month
‚Ä¢ Accommodation Fee
‚Ä¢ Book Allowance

That's why it's not worth it. https://t.co/tLBCNxr47P

Text:
Berapa peruntukan bantuan zakat IPT kali ini?

Local universiti : RM4 juta
Universiti luar negara : RM1 juta

Jadi sehingga threshold tu belum dicapai, masih boleh memohon.

RM700 dan RM2500 tu sesuatu yang besar bagi student. Terutama student2 di Mesir dan Jordan.
Translated Text:
How much is the IPT's zakat aid allocation this time?

Local university: RM4 million
Overseas universities: RM1 million

So until the threshold has not been reached, you can still apply.

RM700 and RM2500 is a big deal for students. Especially students in Egypt and Jordan.

Text:
@mhdrep_ Ada tajaan pun boleh je mohon asalkan cukup syarat. Syarat utama Had Kifayah keluarga tu within range yang ditetapkan.

Had Kifayah + RM5k = Local
Had Kifayah + RM7k = Overseas.

Contoh.

Had Kifayah family : RM2000
Income ayah : RM6000 (+4000)

Layak dapat bantuan.
Translated Text:
@mhdrep_ If there is sponsorship, you can apply as long as there are enough conditions. The main condition is that the family's income limit is within the set range.

Sufficient limit + RM5k = Local
Sufficient limit + RM7k = Overseas.

Example.

Family income limit: RM2000
Father's income: RM6000 (+4000)

Deserve help.

80% kehidupan berumahtangga ni sebenarnya berborak je.

Kalau part komunikasi tu dah sukar, banyak perkara akan bermasalah.
Translated Text:
And also choose people who we are comfortable and enjoy chatting with him üòä.

80% of married life is actually chatting.

Time to eat, want to sleep, in the car, discuss children's affairs, finances, old age etc.

If the communication part is difficult, many things will be problematic.

Text:
Ada orang yang kelihatan baik. Tapi kurang sesuai dengan kita.

Contohnya terlalu pendiam, panas baran, tak pandai buat keputusan penting, tak seronok diajak berbual dsb.

Jadi walaupun dia dah pilih kita, kena juga buat pilihan sebaiknya.

Ia komitmen sampai akhirat.
Translated Text:
There are good looking people. But it doesn't suit us.

For example, too quiet, hot-tempered, not good at making important decisions, not fun to talk to, etc.

So even if he has chosen us, we have to make the best choice.

It is a commitment until the afterlife.

Text:
@zhdmmr Waalaikumussalam,

Haul = Tempoh Setahun

Contoh tahun 2021, Haul saya pada 31 Disember ini.

Jadi semua harta yang saya miliki pada tempoh setahun (1/1 - 31/12), saya kira nilainya dan keluarkan zakat. Emas, saham, perniagaan, simpanan kira pada masa yang sama.
Translated Text:
@zhdmmr Peace be upon you,

Haul = One Year Period

Example of 2021, my Haul on December 31.

So all the property that I have during the period of one year (1/1 - 31/12), I calculate the value and pay zakat. Gold, stocks, business, savings count at the same time.

Text:
Kesilapan terbesar?

Berasa anak boleh tanggung kita waktu itu.

Sedangkan zaman sekarang usia 30-35 tahun pun ramai masih struggle financially untuk sara diri dan keluarga.

Apatah lagi nak sara kedua ibu bapa.

Anda rasa itu bakal berubah? Mungkin anda yg masih menyara mereka.
Translated Text:
Biggest mistake?

Feeling that the child can take care of us at that time.

Whereas nowadays, even at the age of 30-35, many still struggle financially to support themselves and their families.

Not to mention supporting both parents.

Do you think that will change? Maybe you are the one who is still supporting them.

Text:
Jadi.

Salah satu financial goal yang setiap orang kena ada adalah;

Mempunyai pendapatan yang cukup selepas bersara.

Contoh. Setiap bulan ada passive income RM5-10k selama 15 tahun (jangkaan usia 75 tahun).

Ini kena start fikir pada usia 30 tahun. Buatlah apa cara sekalipun.
Translated Text:
So.

One of the financial goals that everyone should have is;

Have enough income after retirement.

Example. Every month there is a passive income of RM5-10k for 15 years (expected age 75).

This should start thinking at the age of 30. Do whatever it takes.

Text:
Ngeri juga bila lihat ramai buat loan rumah sampai usia 65-70 tahun sekarang. Sebulan bayar RM2K+.

Sebab beli rumah (dan kereta) mahal - saving kurang - takde duit nak invest.

Ketika bersara, guna majoriti duit KWSP settlekan hutang. Tak fikir hidup 20 tahun lagi tanpa income.
Translated Text:
It's also scary when you see many people taking home loans until they are 65-70 years old now. Pay RM2K+ per month.

Because buying a house (and car) is expensive - less savings - no money to invest.

Text:

'Hidup' mula menyala di alam lain.

Hidup sebelum mati itu penting. Tetapi hidup selepas mati itu lebih penting. Kerana ia abadi.
Translated Text:
Dying in Islam is not an end, but a beginning to a life that will never die again.

'Life' began to ignite in another realm.

Life before death is important. But life after death is more important. Because it is eternal.

Text:
Kena ada empati. Musim Covid ni ramai yang baru belajar berniaga.

Bagitau je kalau masakan terlalu masin, manis, kena perbaiki sana sini. Mereka pasti hargai komen kita.

Kadangkala kita juga kena terima, taste dan expectation orang ni berbeza-beza.

Kita rasa sedap, orang tak.
Translated Text:
There has to be empathy. This Covid season, many people are just learning to do business.

Just tell me if the food is too salty, too sweet, you have to fix it here and there. They will definitely appreciate our comments.

Sometimes we also have to accept that people's tastes and expectations are different.

We taste good, people don't.

Text:

‚ÄúRasulullah TIDAK PERNAH MENGHINA MAKANAN sama sekali.

Jika baginda mengingini makanan itu, baginda akan makan. Jika baginda tidak suka, baginda akan meninggalkannya.‚Äù

(Sahih Muslim:3851)

Kita ikut cara Rasulullah.
Translated Text:
The easiest way is to follow the way of the Messenger of Allah.

In a hadith.

"The Messenger of God NEVER INSULTED FOOD at all.

If he desires the food, he will eat it. If he doesn't like it, he will leave it."

(Sahih Muslim:3851)

We follow the way of the Prophet.

Text:
Sejak tahun 2014 sehingga harini, takde sorang pun yang mengedar dadah menjalani hukuman mati.

Maksudnya, proses PEMANSUHAN HUKUMAN MATI memang sedang diusahakan.

Mungkin diganti min 30 tahun penjara.

Kita doa semoga ia terlaksana. Ini tugas Ahli Parlimen. Bukan lawyer+Hakim.
Translated Text:
Since 2014 until today, no one who trafficked drugs has been sentenced to death.

In other words, the process of ABOLISHING THE DEATH PENALTY is indeed being worked on.

Maybe replaced by a minimum of 30 years in prison.

We pray that it will happen. This is the duty of Parliamentarians. Not a lawyer+Judge.

Text:
Tugas kita desak wakil rakyat kita luluskan. Sambil bagi kesedaran.

Sebab dulu ada satu survey dari 22,000 respondan kat Malaysia, 82% TIDAK SETUJU hukuman mati dihapuskan.

Mungkin masa tu popular kes rogol budak bawah umur dan bunuh.

Camne nak seimbangkan?

Begitulah.
Translated Text:
Our job is to urge our people's representatives to approve. While for awareness.

Because there used to be a survey of 22,000 respondents in Malaysia, 82% DISAGREE that the death penalty should be abolished.

Maybe at that time, cases of rape and murder of minors were popular.

How do you want to balance it?

That's it.
